{title: What Child Is This}
{artist: John Denver}
{composer: Written by William Dix}

[Em]What child is this who [D7]laid to rest
On [Em]Mary's lap is [B7]sleeping
Whom [Em]angels greet with [D7]anthems sweet
While [Em]shepherds [B7]watch are [Em]keeping
[G]This this is [D7]Christ the king
Whom [Em]shepherds guard and [B7]angels sing
[G]Haste haste to [D7]bring Him laud
The [Em]Babe the [B7]Son of [Em]Mary
Why lies He in such [D7]mean estate
Where [Em]ox and ass are [B7]feeding
Good [Em]Christian fear for [D7]sinners here
The [Em]silent [B7]word is [Em]pleading
Repeat #2
So bring Him incense [D7]gold and myrrh
Come [Em]peasant king to [B7]own Him
The [Em]King of kings sal[D7]vation brings
Let [Em]loving [B7]hearts en[Em]throne Him
Repeat #2